
question 2. Where to attach the script tag:   
<html>
<head></head>
<body>
<h1 id="test">Hello World!</h1>
</body>
</html>
Given the above html, find out what happens when you try to access the element h1 in javascript (using document.getElementById) and change its content to “Goodbye World” when the script is attached:

 ---------------in the head tag-----------------
 
<html>

<head>

<script>
document.getElementById("test").innerHTML="Goodbye World"
</script>

</head>

<body>
<h1 id="test">Hello World!</h1>
</body>
</html>


OUTPUT -> Hello World

-----------------at the start of the body tag--------------------

 
<html>
<head>
<body>

<script>
document.getElementById("test").innerHTML="Goodbye World"
</script>

<h1 id="test">Hello World!</h1>

</body>
</html>

OUTPUT -> Hello World

---------------- at the end of the body tag---------------

  
<html>
<head>
<body>

<h1 id="test">Hello World!</h1>
<script>
document.getElementById("test").innerHTML="Goodbye World"
</script>

</body>
</html>

OUTPUT -> Goodbye World


